# once fires exactly one trigger `delay` seconds after start. At tickrate 100,
# elapsed at tick T = T/100. The trigger fires on the first tick where
# elapsed >= delay, for one tick only. delay=0.045 s -> fires at tick 5
# (0.05 >= 0.045; tick 4 = 0.04 < 0.045). The delay is chosen off an exact tick
# boundary so float rounding can't shift the fire tick.
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[once]
    delay   = 0.045
    trigger = O1
>>>
@0 expect O1 0
@1 expect O1 0
@2 expect O1 0
@3 expect O1 0
@4 expect O1 0
@5 expect O1 1
@6 expect O1 0
@7 expect O1 0
@10 expect O1 0
